President Joe Biden has announced his intention to nominate Charlotte A. Burrows as a Member of the Equal Employment Opportunity Commission (EEOC). Burrows currently serves as the Chair of the EEOC and has been working to enhance the enforcement of all laws within the EEOC's jurisdiction. She has focused on combating retaliation, ensuring compliance with workplace civil rights laws regarding artificial intelligence and other technologies, and expanding employment opportunities for underserved communities. Burrows has a background in civil rights, having previously served as Associate Deputy Attorney General at the Department of Justice (DOJ), General Counsel for Civil and Constitutional Rights to Senator Edward M. Kennedy, and in various roles in the DOJ's Civil Rights Division. She holds degrees from Princeton University and Yale Law School.